cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of time shifts in noise-based logic systems, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The idea of increasing the number of dimensions of the logic space also relates to the study of high-dimensional data analysis (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of time shifts to change commutative operations into non-commuting ones, which is a concept that can be applied in neural networks (cs.NE).
